main event: A civilian witness observed a single unidentified object in the sky for approximately 3 minutes and 30 seconds.
interesting points: The object appeared solid and was brighter than the brightest stars.
The object changed brightness and left a trail.
The object hovered and broke up into parts or exploded.
The observation occurred during daylight hours with a clear, sunny sky.
The witness used binoculars to observe the object.
